            "bio": "Wolf Gunther Plaut (1 November 1912 – 8 February 2012), born in Münster, Germany, was an American Reform rabbi and scholar based in Canada. Rabbi Plaut served Holy Blossom Temple in Toronto until 1978. His popular Torah commentary is widely established in the Reform movement.",
